
[1]sclerotic

   SCLEROT'IC, a. [Gr. hard; hardness.]

   Hard; firm; as the sclerotic coat or tunicle of the eye.

                               SCLEROT'IC, n.

   1. The firm white outer coat of the eye.

   2. A medicine which hardens and consolidates the parts to which it is
   applied.
